Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
When I select 'Male' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
Then I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I go to Page 3 and select 'Yes' in Contrast enhanced
And I click on 'Sequences' tab and select 'Individual' button
And I select 'DWI' in 'Weighting' dropdown
And I go to Page 05 of Pelvic MRI
And I click on 'Finding' radio button
And dropdown below 'Finding' is enabled

When I select 'Penis mass' from the dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'I describe' button is preselected

When I select 'I know' button
And I click on 'Charakterization II'
Then 'Signal loss/flow void' checkbox is enabled
And 'Necrosis' checkbox is enabled

And 'Strong' radio button is enabled
And 'Low' radio button is enabled
And 'No' radio button is enabled

And 'Marginal contrast enhancement' checkbox is enabled
And 'Diffusion restriction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Corpus spongiosum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Corpus cavernosum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Urethra' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tunica albuginea' checkbox is enabled
And 'Exulceration' checkbox is enabled
And 'Scrotum' checkbox is enabled

When I click on 'Signal loss/flow void' checkbox
Then 'Diffuse' radio button is enabled
And 'Focal' radio button is enabled

When I click on 'Strong' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

When I click on 'Low' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Corpus cavernosum' checkbox
Then 'Right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Scrotum' checkbox
Then 'Testicles' checkbox is enabled
And 'Epididymis' checkbox is enabled
